title: Mighty Quinn: October 23
text:
The Mighty Quinn
The Mighty One himself.
What are the odds of this surviving at Sportsmania Pub in Rosedale? Over half a million dollars in one dollar bills and all these years later it’s still there?
“McGuire’s Irish Brewery in Pensacola, Fla. Should you find yourself in McGuire’s broke, unsure of where your next beer is coming from, try to resist the urge to strip a few dollars off the ceiling: there you’ll find $550,000 worth of dollar bills.
“In 1977 McGuire’s began as a small neighborhood pub in a shopping center. When Molly McGuire, the bar’s owner, made her first one dollar tip, she stuck it to the ceiling for good luck. Friends of the pub added to the collection and it soon became tradition. And after many years had passed, those dollars amounted to $550,000. How long it took to count all those is unclear.” (courtesy irishcentral.com)
Mighty was waiting on the 49ers (+6) on Thursday and likes the Blue Jays on Friday. The deficit is 833 sirignanos.
